This expects the extracted atoms to be a single atom with length 3 and bytes [0x11, 0x22, 0x33].

The bug is in the atoms.c file at the point where we update `best_atom`. When a better atom is found (line 1066), we copy the bytes and masks but don't update the length (line 1075 in the current buggy version, which is missing the `best_atom.length = atom.length;` line).

Without updating the length, if there was a previous best_atom with a different length, the best_atom would have the old length combined with new byte/mask data, which is incorrect.

